d compromise","tr":"fayud'hinūna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":10,"verseKey":"68:10","juz":29,"arabic":"وَلَا تُطِعْ كُلَّ حَلَّافٍ مَّهِينٍ","fr":"N’écoute pas celui qui jure à tout propos, et qui est ignoble,","en":"And do not obey every worthless habitual swearer","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"Et (fais) non","en":"And (do) not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"تُطِعْ","fr":"obéir","en":"obey","tr":"tuṭiʿ","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"كُلَّ","fr":"chaque","en":"every","tr":"kulla","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"حَلَّافٍۢ","fr":"grand jureur","en":"habitual swearer","tr":"ḥallāfin","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"مَّهِينٍ","fr":"sans valeur","en":"worthless","tr":"mahīnin","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":11,"verseKey":"68:11","juz":29,"arabic":"هَمَّازٍ مَّشَّآءٍۭ بِنَمِيمٍ","fr":"le diffamateur intempérant, le grand colporteur de calomnies,","en":"[And] scorner, going about with malicious gossip -","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"هَمَّازٍۢ","fr":"Diffamateur","en":"Defamer","tr":"hammāzin","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"مَّشَّآءٍۭ","fr":"allant au sujet de","en":"going about","tr":"mashāin","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"بِنَمِيمٍۢ","fr":"avec malicious gossip","en":"with malicious gossip","tr":"binamīmin","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":12,"verseKey":"68:12","juz":29,"arabic":"مَّنَّاعٍ لِّلْخَيْرِ مُعْتَدٍ أَثِيمٍ","fr":"l’adversaire du bien, l’agresseur et le pécheur","en":"A preventer of good, transgressing and sinful,","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"مَّنَّاعٍۢ","fr":"Un Celui qui empêche","en":"A preventer","tr":"mannāʿin","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"لِّلْخَيْرِ","fr":"de (le) bon","en":"of (the) good","tr":"lil'khayri","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"مُعْتَدٍ","fr":"transgresseur","en":"transgressor","tr":"muʿ'tadin","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"أَثِيمٍ","fr":"pécheur","en":"sinful","tr":"athīmin","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":13,"verseKey":"68:13","juz":29,"arabic":"عُتُلٍّۭ بَعْدَ ذَٰلِكَ زَنِيمٍ","fr":"brutal, et de surcroît bâtard.","en":"Cruel, moreover, and an illegitimate pretender.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"عُتُلٍّۭ","fr":"Cruel","en":"Cruel","tr":"ʿutullin","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"بَعْدَ","fr":"après","en":"after","tr":"baʿda","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"ذَٰلِكَ","fr":"(tout) que","en":"(all) that","tr":"dhālika","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"زَنِيمٍ","fr":"tout à fait inutile","en":"utterly useless","tr":"zanīmin","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":14,"verseKey":"68:14","juz":29,"arabic":"أَن كَانَ ذَا مَالٍ وَبَنِينَ","fr":"Même quand il possède des biens (en abondance) et de (nombreux) enfants,","en":"Because he is a possessor of wealth and children,","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"أَن","fr":"Car","en":"Because","tr":"an","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"كَانَ","fr":"(il) est","en":"(he) is","tr":"kāna","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"ذَا","fr":"un possesseur","en":"a possessor","tr":"dhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"مَالٍۢ","fr":"(de) richesse","en":"(of) wealth","tr":"mālin","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"وَبَنِينَ","fr":"et enfants","en":"and children","tr":"wabanīna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":15,"verseKey":"68:15","juz":29,"arabic":"إِذَا تُتْلَىٰ عَلَيْهِ ءَايَـٰتُنَا قَالَ أَسَـٰطِيرُ ٱلْأَوَّلِينَ","fr":"il dit en entendant réciter Nos versets : « Ce ne sont que fables d’anciens ! »","en":"When Our verses are recited to him, he says, \"Legends of the former peoples.\"","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"إِذَا","fr":"Quand","en":"When","tr":"idhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"تُتْلَىٰ","fr":"sont récités","en":"are recited","tr":"tut'lā","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"عَلَيْهِ","fr":"à lui","en":"to him","tr":"ʿalayhi","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"ءَايَـٰتُنَا","fr":"Nos Versets","en":"Our Verses","tr":"āyātunā","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"قَالَ","fr":"il dit","en":"he says","tr":"qāla","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"أَسَـٰطِيرُ","fr":"Récits","en":"Stories","tr":"asāṭīru","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"ٱلْأَوَّلِينَ","fr":"(des) anciens","en":"(of) the former (people)","tr":"l-awalīna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":16,"verseKey":"68:16","juz":29,"arabic":"سَنَسِمُهُۥ عَلَى ٱلْخُرْطُومِ","fr":"Nous lui marquerons le nez.","en":"We will brand him upon the snout.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"سَنَسِمُهُۥ","fr":"Nous va brandon lui","en":"We will brand him","tr":"sanasimuhu","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"عَلَى","fr":"sur","en":"on","tr":"ʿalā","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"ٱلْخُرْطُومِ","fr":"le snout","en":"the snout","tr":"l-khur'ṭūmi","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":17,"verseKey":"68:17","juz":29,"arabic":"إِنَّا بَلَوْنَـٰهُمْ كَمَا بَلَوْنَآ أَصْحَـٰبَ ٱلْجَنَّةِ إِذْ أَقْسَمُوا۟ لَيَصْرِمُنَّهَا مُصْبِحِينَ","fr":"Nous les avons éprouvés comme Nous avions autrefois éprouvé les propriétaires du jardin et qui s’étaient juré de procéder à sa récolte au petit jour","en":"Indeed, We have tried them as We tried the companions of the garden, when they swore to cut its fruit in the [early] morning","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"إِنَّا","fr":"Certes, Nous","en":"Indeed, We","tr":"innā","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"بَلَوْنَـٰهُمْ","fr":"ont éprouvé eux","en":"have tried them","tr":"balawnāhum","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"كَمَا","fr":"comme","en":"as","tr":"kamā","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"بَلَوْنَآ","fr":"Nous éprouvé","en":"We tried","tr":"balawnā","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"أَصْحَـٰبَ","fr":"(le) compagnons","en":"(the) companions","tr":"aṣḥāba","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"ٱلْجَنَّةِ","fr":"(de) le jardin","en":"(of) the garden","tr":"l-janati","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"إِذْ","fr":"quand","en":"when","tr":"idh","isWaqf":false},{"position":8,"ar":"أَقْسَمُوا۟","fr":"ils jura","en":"they swore","tr":"aqsamū","isWaqf":false},{"position":9,"ar":"لَيَصْرِمُنَّهَا","fr":"à arracher son fruit","en":"to pluck its fruit","tr":"layaṣrimunnahā","isWaqf":false},{"position":10,"ar":"مُصْبِحِينَ","fr":"(dans le) matin","en":"(in the) morning","tr":"muṣ'biḥīna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":18,"verseKey":"68:18","juz":29,"arabic":"وَلَا يَسْتَثْنُونَ","fr":"sans restreindre (leur serment)","en":"Without making exception.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"وَلَا","fr":"Et non","en":"And not","tr":"walā","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"يَسْتَثْنُونَ","fr":"faisant exception","en":"making exception","tr":"yastathnūna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":19,"verseKey":"68:19","juz":29,"arabic":"فَطَافَ عَلَيْهَا طَآئِفٌ مِّن رَّبِّكَ وَهُمْ نَآئِمُونَ","fr":"Un fléau venu de la part de ton Seigneur fondit sur le jardin pendant qu’ils dormaient.","en":"So there came upon it [i.e., the garden] an affliction from your Lord while they were asleep.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"فَطَافَ","fr":"Donc là vint","en":"So there came","tr":"faṭāfa","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"عَلَيْهَا","fr":"sur cela","en":"upon it","tr":"ʿalayhā","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"طَآئِفٌۭ","fr":"un visitation","en":"a visitation","tr":"ṭāifun","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"مِّن","fr":"de","en":"from","tr":"min","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"رَّبِّكَ","fr":"votre Seigneur","en":"your Lord","tr":"rabbika","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"وَهُمْ","fr":"tandis qu'ils","en":"while they","tr":"wahum","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"نَآئِمُونَ","fr":"étaient endormi","en":"were asleep","tr":"nāimūna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":20,"verseKey":"68:20","juz":29,"arabic":"فَأَصْبَحَتْ كَٱلصَّرِيمِ","fr":"Au matin, (le jardin) était complètement ravagé.","en":"And it became as though reaped.","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"فَأَصْبَحَتْ","fr":"Donc cela devint","en":"So it became","tr":"fa-aṣbaḥat","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"كَٱلصَّرِيمِ","fr":"comme si moissonna","en":"as if reaped","tr":"kal-ṣarīmi","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":21,"verseKey":"68:21","juz":29,"arabic":"فَتَنَادَوْا۟ مُصْبِحِينَ","fr":"En se levant avec le jour, ils s’appelèrent les uns les autres :","en":"And they called one another at morning,","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"فَتَنَادَوْا۟","fr":"Et ils appelé l'un l'autre","en":"And they called one another","tr":"fatanādaw","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"مُصْبِحِينَ","fr":"(à) matin","en":"(at) morning","tr":"muṣ'biḥīna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":22,"verseKey":"68:22","juz":29,"arabic":"أَنِ ٱغْدُوا۟ عَلَىٰ حَرْثِكُمْ إِن كُنتُمْ صَـٰرِمِينَ","fr":"« Allez vite à votre champ si vous comptez (toujours) en achever la récolte. »","en":"[Saying], \"Go early to your crop if you would cut the fruit.\"","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"أَنِ","fr":"Cela","en":"That","tr":"ani","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"ٱغْدُوا۟","fr":"Aller tôt","en":"Go early","tr":"igh'dū","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"عَلَىٰ","fr":"à","en":"to","tr":"ʿalā","isWaqf":false},{"position":4,"ar":"حَرْثِكُمْ","fr":"votre crop","en":"your crop","tr":"ḥarthikum","isWaqf":false},{"position":5,"ar":"إِن","fr":"si","en":"if","tr":"in","isWaqf":false},{"position":6,"ar":"كُنتُمْ","fr":"vous irait","en":"you would","tr":"kuntum","isWaqf":false},{"position":7,"ar":"صَـٰرِمِينَ","fr":"arracher (le) fruit","en":"pluck (the) fruit","tr":"ṣārimīna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":23,"verseKey":"68:23","juz":29,"arabic":"فَٱنطَلَقُوا۟ وَهُمْ يَتَخَـٰفَتُونَ","fr":"Ils s’élancèrent aussitôt en se disant tout bas les uns aux autres :","en":"So they set out, while lowering their voices,","words":[{"position":1,"ar":"فَٱنطَلَقُوا۟","fr":"Donc ils alla","en":"So they went","tr":"fa-inṭalaqū","isWaqf":false},{"position":2,"ar":"وَهُمْ","fr":"tandis qu'ils","en":"while they","tr":"wahum","isWaqf":false},{"position":3,"ar":"يَتَخَـٰفَتُونَ","fr":"baissa (leur) voix","en":"lowered (their) voices","tr":"yatakhāfatūna","isWaqf":false}]},{"ayah":24,"verseKey":"68:24","juz":29,"arabic":"أَن لَّا يَدْخُلَنَّهَا ٱلْيَوْمَ عَلَيْكُم مِّسْكِينٌ","fr":"« Que nul pauvre n’y entre aujourd’hui ! »","en":"[Saying], \"There will surely not enter it today upon you [any] poor person.\"","words":[{"position":1,"